Title: A Two Fluid Description of the Quantum Hall Soliton
Authors: Ben Freivogel, Leonard Susskind and Nicolaos Toumbas
Comments: 28 pages, 2 figures
Report-no: SU-ITP-01/25, SLAC-PUB-8657
\\
  We show that the Quantum Hall Soliton constructed in \cite{giantbob} is
stable under small perturbations. We find that creating quasiparticles actually
lowers the energy of the system, and discuss whether this indicates an
instability on the time scales relevant to the problem.
